body:
I've come up with a little workaround for this by just using this little script in a cron job to regularly remove these sync-conflict files:

```
#!/bin/bash
/usr/bin/find /home/some_directory/thats/synced -name '*.sync-conflict-20*' -exec rm -f {} \;
```

The use case here is syncing from a Windows laptop up to a VPS, where the files are never touched on the VPS (so one-way sync in effect). So in other situations (e.g. syncing important documents between your laptop and desktop) this kind of thing might not be the best idea.
